Steps:
1. add jar to pom
<!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.github.ulisesbocchio/jasypt-spring-boot-starter -->
<dependency>
   <groupId>com.github.ulisesbocchio</groupId>
   <artifactId>jasypt-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>
   <version>1.9</version>
</dependency>

2. Encrypt wanted password in command line. set wanted password under 'input', set master key under password
java -cp ~/.m2/repository/org/jasypt/jasypt/1.9.2/jasypt-1.9.2.jar org.jasypt.intf.cli.JasyptPBEStringEncryptionCLI input="admin" password=master algorithm=PBEWithMD5AndDES

3. Put encrypted text in wanted field using ENC() in yml/config file
password: ENC(2r7r/U551IldTXIjht8aYA==)

4. Alsos add password key as follows:
jasypt.encryptor.password: master